I’ve resolved to reduce my #fastfashion consumption even more & focus on eco-conscious, ethical small businesses. That doesn’t mean I need to go buy a whole new wardrobe. Rather I’m selecting pieces I am capable of altering, repurposing linens&fabric, & donating unfitting items.

Like I keep reminding myself: I don’t need to purchase toiletry containers despite all the Cadence ads I’m getting. I have appropriately sized and functional empty minis that products can go into. Thereby reducing my own waste generation. #Sustainable
This is a reminder that making more #Sustainable and eco-conscious with goods and purchasing doesn’t mean purchase replacements for things you own: reduce, reuse, recycle.

My unconfessed favorites from both adolescence and young adulthood say a lot more about what I was actually going through than the content I admitted to.

As a whole this is a good reason to reread favorites or titles from adolescence when you've entered another phase of life. Different meanings, lessons, and comfort rise to the surface; your perspective changes. What is profound shifts.

I feel like part of deconstructing is reexamining media that was engaged with from a skewed POV. Like books I read as a teen that helped me and opened perspectives subconsciously, while I left low star reviews because of "the content" growing up. #exvangelical

Because the minutia is important with ASD, I am excruciatingly aware of all of it. Because it stacks up to affecting my day to day. So I do what I can to be as prepared as I can while away from home, to help future Siri. #ActuallyAutistic

The minutia I exert thought over is compulsive, it’s stressful, and I’m constantly on the brink of a panic attack. Not for what is, but for what might be…but also not about something “important”. #ActuallyAutistic
Anticipating to hate some clothes, knowing there’s things I will pack and not use. Trying to pack so that things are best distributed for use and restrictions. #ActuallyAutistic

But really the biggest difficulty for me is packing. Weight and size limitations coupled with my need to be prepared for anything. I don’t know how I’ll feel, what my sensory issues might be on any given day. #ActuallyAutistic
I love to travel but there’s certain challenges with ASD. I have to normalize disruption, expect delay, so anything is “routine” and able to be handled. #actuallyautistic

The final verdict? Wow for reasons good and bad. I can tell a lot of super talented and amazing people worked on it. The physical effects, Baba Yaga, the giant fight, Diamo and Alice were great. #SiriLiveTweets #Hellboy2019
Okay okay I had to stop. It was exhausting and I couldn’t look away. The second half? Better. Likely because it was all action. #Hellboy2019 #SiriLiveTweets
I’m conflicted because the physical special effects are overall SOLID but the computer generated effects are....not good. #Hellboy2019 #SiriLiveTweets
Alice is a delightful breath of fresh air. #Hellboy2019 #SiriLiveTweets
Hellboy vs. the 3 Giants is what I’ve been waiting for. And despite the style...and the CG...it otherwise feels rather true to form. #SiriLiveTweets #Hellboy2019
Just when I think I can take a moment to eat my dinner, there’s a dissected Nimue strewn about a couch watching reality tv. #SiriLiveTweets #Hellboy2019

Ah Okay Yeah. “Maybe we should all just stab Hellboy”. 
Maybe...we shouldn’t have rebooted this franchise? Because I was promised a closer following of the comics and this is a B Movie rampantly devoid of any emotion or depth of character. #Hellboy2019 #SiriLiveTweets
Gruagach looks so good...until literally any moment his Scooby Doo CG face is moving or talking. Also: what amidst all the realms is this soundtrack????? #Hellboy2019 #SiriLiveTweets

Excuse me while I drown out my agony with mashed potatoes and gravy. Oh wait, it just got overly gorey. And talking pig head looks like circa a decade ago live action Scooby Doo? WHAT IS HAPPENING. #Hellboy2019 #SiriLiveTweets
Oh. Oh no. Ohhhhhhhh no why are all the flashbacks so so so so bad. This is...unacceptably campy. Why why why. #Hellboy2019 #SiriLiveTweets
Gotta give props to the set dressing for the Osiris Club though. #Hellboy2019 #SiriLiveTweets
For the record I’m a hardcore long time fan of the comics. This is...painful. #Hellboy2019 #SiriLiveTweets
So here I am, because tweeting is less invasive to the viewing experience of my family members, when the other option is screeching outbursts. #Hellboy2019 #SiriLiveTweets
I mean opening narration both self aware and boring? Cue my agonized face palm. #Hellboy2019 #SiriLiveTweets

We opened with B-Movie performance and dialogue in a sequence which had me screeching the only way to save it were if it were an imagining of a tale in the mind of childhood Hellboy, as narrated by Prof. Broom. #Hellboy2019 #SiriLiveTweets
What even is the vibe of this movie? What is the ambiance? What am I even supposed to be thinking/feeling?? #Hellboy2019 #SiriLiveTweets
